The Three Laws of Robotics
The first law: Robots must not harm people, nor cause harm to people by inaction;
The second law: without violating the first law, robots should obey all human commands;
The third law: Without violating the first and second laws, robots should protect their own safety.It's easy to see that the third law is almost never seen in the film, and the main thing is an extension of the first law. The second law is only piggybacked.Why was the original work scolded? It's not because it violates the law of three, or because the content of the movie really sucks, but because it's trying to cram some of the other books that belong to the whole big series into a short movie, so although the movie has the visual sense of the original in some places, the same plot is used to express different, even completely opposite things, which makes people very speechless.
